The Dashboard is the main page of the system that provides users with a quick overview of important business information. It displays key metrics and real-time data to help users monitor inventory, sales, and overall system performance without navigating to different pages.
Main Functions:
Displays the total number of products, suppliers, customers, and sales.
Shows low-stock and out-of-stock product alerts.
Provides daily, weekly, monthly, or yearly sales summaries.
Displays recent transactions and activities.
Shows charts and graphs for sales trends and inventory status.
Provides quick access to frequently used modules such as Products, Suppliers, POS, Reports, and Settings.
Displays notifications and important system updates.
The dashboard helps users make informed decisions by presenting essential business information in a clear, organized, and easy-to-understand interface. It serves as the central hub of the Inventory Management and Point of Sale (POS) System, allowing administrators and staff to monitor operations efficiently.
